text:
Wanted to share out an email list/community that I belong to called systers, it’s open to women working in technology all over the world. People email there with general questions about working in tech, discussions on diversity and inclusion, and all other kinds of cool stuff.  

<http://anitaborg.org/get-involved/systers/>

attachments.title: Systers - Anita Borg Institute
attachments.text: Join Systers It’s important to know that you are not alone. Systers is a forum for all women involved in the technical aspects of computing. The community has over 6,000 members from at least 60 countries around the world. We welcome the participation of women technologists of all ages and at any stage of their... Read more »
